examples/support_bot/README.md
     1â†’# Support bot
     3â†’This example is a customer service bot which includes a user interface agent and a help center agent with several tools.
     4â†’This example uses the helper function `run_demo_loop`, which allows us to create an interactive Swarm session.
     5â†’
     6â†’## Overview
     8â†’The support bot consists of two main agents:
     9â†’
    10â†’1. **User Interface Agent**: Handles initial user interactions and directs them to the help center agent based on their needs.
    11â†’2. **Help Center Agent**: Provides detailed help and support using various tools and integrated with a Qdrant VectorDB for documentation retrieval.
    12â†’
    13â†’## Setup
    15â†’To start the support bot:
    16â†’
    17â†’1. Ensure Docker is installed and running on your system.
    18â†’2. Install the necessary additional libraries:
    19â†’
    20â†’```shell
    21â†’make install
    22â†’```
    23â†’
    24â†’3. Initialize docker
    25â†’
    26â†’```shell
    27â†’docker-compose up -d
    28â†’```
    29â†’
    30â†’4. Prepare the vector DB:
    31â†’
    32â†’```shell
    33â†’make prep
    34â†’```
    35â†’
    36â†’5. Run the main scripy:
    37â†’
    38â†’```shell
    39â†’make run
    40â†’```

